    "summary": "I work as an actor, writer, director, singer and producer in the performing arts.\nI work in the field of writing new theatre texts, interdisciplinary work and in the field of opera and musictheatre. I also teach and consult on these matters.\n\nBesides working with or at Company's like La Mama experimental theatre international, Dutch National Opera, Nederlandse Reisopera, La Monnaie/De Munt, Oper Neuk\u00f6ln, Zina, De Nieuw Amsterdam or De Veenfabriek\nI spend a lot of my time running my own music-theater company Het Geluid Maastricht.\n\nWith www.hetgeluid.eu \nGable Roelofsen recently won the prince Bernhard Culture fund inspiration prize Limburg 2015 And the Berliner Opernpreis 2016.\n\nThe commoning project Common Carnaval, in which new and old Maastricht citizens meet around collectively designing and re-designing the old carnaval tradition won the Dutch charlamagne youth prize (of the European Parliament) as well as the Willem the Vliegerpenning. \n\nMost recently Het Geluid won two 2017 Dutch Game awards for Weltatem a mixed media opera.  www.weltatem.eu\n\nEducation: BA in theatre performance Toneelacademie Maastricht, Lincoln Center Theater Directorslab New York City, apt-apass postgraduate school for performing arts Belgium (artistic research in new musictheatre), academie de festival d'aix en Provence, Operamanagement Course of Opera Europa Festival Peralada\n\nMr Roelofsen is an arts-consultant at the Dutch Arts Council and a guest-lecturer at Iarts Maastricht (Interdisciplinary arts, science and enterpreneurial education at Hs Zuyd uni of applied sciences) And at the Master Dramaturgy of the university of Amsterdam.\n\nAs of summer 2017 Gable Roelofsen is chairman of the Dutch art council committee that advises the Dutch Ministry of culture on the future of the Dutch opera and musictheatre sector.",
